===============================================================================

Thumbsy has been installed! 

Next steps:

1. Run the migration:
   rails db:migrate

2. Add thumbsy methods to your models:

   # For models that can be voted on:
   class Post < ApplicationRecord
     votable
   end

   # For models that can vote:
   class User < ApplicationRecord
     voter
   end

3. Usage examples:

   # Voting
   @post.vote_up(@user)
   @post.vote_down(@user, comment: "Not helpful")
   
   # Or from voter perspective:
   @user.vote_up_for(@post)
   @user.vote_down_for(@post, comment: "Great post!")

   # Checking votes
   @post.voted_by?(@user)
   @post.up_voted_by?(@user)
   @post.votes_count
   @post.up_votes_count
   @post.votes_score

   # Getting voters
   @post.voters
   @post.up_voters
   @post.down_voters

   # Scopes
   Post.with_votes
   Post.with_up_votes
   Post.with_down_votes
   Post.with_comments

   # Comments on votes
   @post.votes_with_comments
   @post.up_votes_with_comments

For more information, visit: https://github.com/yourusername/thumbsy

===============================================================================
